examples.en: Six and six make twelve.

The clock struck twelve.
Twelve divided by four equals / is three.
Three multiplied by four makes twelve.
Come at twelve (=12 o'clock).

What time is it? It's twelve.
The church clock began to strike twelve.
There are twelve programmes in the series.
We can sit twelve guests at our dinner table.

Between the hours of twelve and four in the morning.
